cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.NI, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses writing a massively concurrent network server, which falls under the domain of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.OS (Operating Systems) - The paper discusses the use of native system threads, which is a core concept in operating systems. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on writing a network server, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses a programming system (CPC) and programming idioms, which are relevant to programming languages. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may touch upon data structures and algorithms used in the implementation of the network server.
